Write a function differenceMaxMin that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the difference between the maximum and minimum value. 
If the array is empty return null.

Example:

differenceMaxMin ([3, 4, 8, 1]) should return 7;
differenceMaxMin ([7, 7]) should return 0;
differenceMaxMin ([2]) should return 0;
differenceMaxMin ([]) should return null;

Solution:

function differenceMaxMin(arr){
  return arr.length === 0 ? null : Math.max(...arr) - Math.min(...arr);
}
